.SH "NAME"
dev_close \- shutdown an interface\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ dev_close('u
.BI "int dev_close(struct\ net_device\ *\ " "dev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device to shutdown
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
This function moves an active device into down state\&. A
\fBNETDEV_GOING_DOWN\fR
is sent to the netdev notifier chain\&. The device is then deactivated and finally a
\fBNETDEV_DOWN\fR
is sent to the notifier chain\&.
